        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(slides): add native slide structure commands",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add `gog slides new-slide` for native themed slides using `CreateSlideRequest` with `--layout` and optional `--index`.\n- Add `gog slides duplicate-slide` using `DuplicateObjectRequest`, with optional `--to-index` handled by an `UpdateSlidesPositionRequest` for the generated duplicate slide ID.\n- Add `gog slides move-slide` using `UpdateSlidesPositionRequest` and required `--to-index`.\n- Include dry-run batchUpdate payloads before auth/API setup, local empty-ID and negative-index validation, JSON output, focused httptest request-capture tests, and regenerated command docs.\n\n## Out of scope\n- The broader element/table/text-style subtree from #826 remains intentionally deferred.\n\n## Manual merge note\nThis should remain manual-merge only until a maintainer verifies the commands against a live Google Slides deck: create a native layout slide, duplicate a template slide and move it with `--to-index`, then move an existing slide with `move-slide`.\n\n## Release note\nAdds first-class native slide creation, duplication, and reordering commands to `gog slides`.\n\nThanks @sebsnyk for the source report.\n\nFixes #826\n",
